    • Method Detail

      • getSubsystemElement

        public List<JAXBElement<? extends SubsystemElement>> getSubsystemElement()
        R13 Gets the value of the subsystemElement property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the subsystemElement property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getSubsystemElement().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<UnaryAssociation> JAXBElement<SubsystemElement> JAXBElement<BinaryAssociation> JAXBElement<Association> JAXBElement<Class> JAXBElement<Relationship> JAXBElement<Generalization>
